President Obama has announced the Presidential Delegation to the Opening Ceremony of the 2012 Olympic Games in London. The delegation will be led by First Lady Michelle Obama, who will be accompanied by Olympic and Paralympic athletes. The First Lady's main focus is to encourage American children to be active in their daily lives and combat childhood obesity. The delegation includes athletes such as Brandi Chastain, Dominique Dawes, Gabriel Diaz de Leon, Grant Hill, and Summer Sanders. The goal is to inspire a generation of young people to get active and reach their fullest potential.